X:1
T:Wedge hairpins - regression test
C:Antony Leedale
%
% REGRESSION (2026-07-16): every wedge START was emitted as <wedge type="stop">, so all
% hairpins were silently dead (starts never appeared; MuseScore showed/played nothing).
% Cause: the start/stop test used `if ')' in d or 'end' in d`, and "end" is a substring of
% cresc-END-o / diminu-END-o / decresc-END-o. Fixed with explicit token sets.
%
% EXPECTED from this file: 4x wedge type="crescendo", 4x type="diminuendo", 8x type="stop",
% strictly alternating start,stop,start,stop... Verify with:
%   python3 abc2xml/abc2xml.py TESTFILES/test_wedge_hairpins.abc | grep -o 'wedge type="[a-z]*"'
%
M:4/4
L:1/4
K:C
V:1 name="Violin"
[V:1] !crescendo(!C D E F!crescendo)! | !diminuendo(!G A B c!diminuendo)! | !<(!C D E F!<)! | !>(!G A B c!>)! | !cresc(!C D E F!cresc)! | !dim(!G A B c!dim)! | !cresc(start)!C D E F!cresc(end)! | !dim(start)!G A B c!dim(end)! |]
